message: Change "all-party, open primary" to "nonpartisan blanket primary," and clarify that the "general election" is, in fact, a runoff. Alaska's new system does not call for "open primaries," i.e., one in which voters do not have to be registered with a party. The system does not call for primaries at all, in fact, as primaries are used to choose party nominees. Hence it also does not make sense to refer to an "all-party primary." More precise would be "all-candidate first round," which is nonsensical
